Package com.atakmap.map.layer.feature.style

Class IconPointStyle

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.atakmap.map.layer.feature.style.Style
      • com.atakmap.map.layer.feature.style.IconPointStyle
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Disposable
    public final class IconPointStyle
extends Style
    Icon style for point geometries. Renders the associated point geometry using the specified icon.

      • IconPointStyle

        public IconPointStyle​(int color,
                      java.lang.String iconUri,
                      float iconWidth,
                      float iconHeight,
                      int alignX,
                      int alignY,
                      float rotation,
                      boolean rotationAbsolute)
        Creates a new icon style with the specified properties.
        Parameters:
        color - The icon color
        iconUri - The icon URI
        iconWidth - The icon render width. Use 0f to render at original width.
        iconHeight - The icon render height. Use 0f to render at original height.
        alignX - The horizontal alignment of the icon. Less than 0 for to the left, 0 for horizontal centered, greater than 0 for to the right
        alignY - The vertical alignment of the icon. Less than 0 for above, 0 for vertically centered, greater than 0 for below
        rotation - The rotation of the icon, in degrees counter clockwise
        rotationAbsolute - true if the rotation is absolute (relative to North), false if the rotation is relative to screen "up".

      • IconPointStyle

                      float offsetY,
                      int alignX,
                      int alignY,
                      float rotation,
                      boolean rotationAbsolute)
        Creates a new icon style with the specified properties.
        Parameters:
        color - The icon color
        iconUri - The icon URI
        iconWidth - The icon render width. Use 0f to render at original width.
        iconHeight - The icon render height. Use 0f to render at original height.
        offsetX - The x-axis pixel offset of the icon from the reference point
        offsetY - The y-axis pixel offset of the icon from the reference point
        alignX - The horizontal alignment of the icon. Less than 0 for to the left, 0 for horizontal centered, greater than 0 for to the right
        alignY - The vertical alignment of the icon. Less than 0 for above, 0 for vertically centered, greater than 0 for below
        rotation - The rotation of the icon, in degrees counter clockwise
        rotationAbsolute - true if the rotation is absolute (relative to North), false if the rotation is relative to screen "up".

        Creates a new icon style with the specified properties.
        Parameters:
        color - The icon color
        iconUri - The icon URI
        scale - scaling to apply to the icon when rendered
        alignX - The horizontal alignment of the icon. Less than 0 for to the left, 0 for horizontal centered, greater than 0 for to the right
        alignY - The vertical alignment of the icon. Less than 0 for above, 0 for vertically centered, greater than 0 for below
        rotation - The rotation of the icon, in degrees counter clockwise
        rotationAbsolute - true if the rotation is absolute (relative to North), false if the rotation is relative to screen "up".

    • Method Detail

      • getColor

        public int getColor()
        Returns the color to be modulated with the icon. Each pixel value in the icon is multiplied by the returned color; a value of 0xFFFFFFFF should be used to render the icon using its original color.
        Returns:
        The icon color.

      • getIconScaling

        public float getIconScaling()
        Returns the scaling to be applied to the icon when rendering. If this returns 0, no scaling is to be applied
        Returns:
        Scale factor to be applied when rendering the icon

      • getIconRotation

        public float getIconRotation()
        Returns the rotation to be applied to the icon. The value of isRotationAbsolute() should be evaluated to correctly interpret the rotation value.
        Returns:
        The rotation of the icon, in degrees counter-clockwise.
        See Also:
        isRotationAbsolute()

      • isRotationAbsolute

        public boolean isRotationAbsolute()
        Returns true if the rotation is absolute (relative to North) or false if the rotation is relative.
        Returns:
        true if the rotation is absolute (relative to North) or false if the rotation is relative to screen "up".

      • getIconUri

        public java.lang.String getIconUri()
        Returns the URI for the icon.
        Returns:

      • getIconAlignmentX

        public int getIconAlignmentX()
        Returns the horizontal alignment for the icon. A value of less-than 0 indicates to the left of the point, a value of 0 is horizontally centered on the point and a value greater than 0 indicates to the right of the point.
        Returns:
        The horizontal alignment for the icon with respect to the point.

      • getIconAligmnentY

        public int getIconAligmnentY()
        Returns the vertical alignment for the icon. A value of less-than 0 indicates above the point, a value of 0 is centered vertically on the point and a value greater than 0 indicates below the point.
        Returns:
        The vertical alignment for the icon with respect to the point.

      • getIconWidth

        public float getIconWidth()
        Returns the rendered width for the icon. If non-zero, the icon will be horizontally scaled to the specified width.
        Returns:
        The rendered width for the icon. If 0f the icon will be rendered at its original width.

      • getIconHeight

        public float getIconHeight()
        Returns the rendered height for the icon. If non-zero, the icon will be vertically scaled to the specified height.
        Returns:
        The rendered height for the icon. If 0f the icon will be rendered at its original height.

      • getIconOffsetX

        public float getIconOffsetX()
        Returns the vertical offset to be applied to the icon when rendering.
        Returns:
        The vertical offset for the icon with respect to the point in pixels

      • getIconOffsetY

        public float getIconOffsetY()
        Returns the horizontal offset to be applied to the icon when rendering.
        Returns:
        The horizontal offset for the icon with respect to the point in pixels
